Cakey base❌ Flawless glowy base✅😍

So apparently, a lot of Korean celebs wrap their face in plastic after skincare and now I get why. I applied the @sheglam_official HydroSlime primer, then wrapped my face for 5 minutes. The plastic creates an occlusive barrier, meaning it traps heat and moisture, helping your skin absorb all the hydration and active ingredients more deeply. It’s like a DIY sheet mask, but way more intense. It’s especially great if your skin is dehydrated or your makeup tends to look cakey or clingy.
My skin felt so fresh and bouncy after and my foundation just melted in, no dryness, no patchy spots. It actually works!💙

Pink Korean Cushion Foundation💕🎀😱 how pretty is this packaging?!😍 @unleashia 
I picked the pink variant, which gives sheer coverage and a gorgeous glow. I’ve used the shade 33N — it’s slightly light for my skin tone, so if you have a similar complexion, I’d recommend going one shade deeper.

This cushion comes in 3 variants:
Pink – sheer coverage + glow
Green – soft glow + medium coverage
Blue – high coverage

Should I try the green or blue one next? Let me know!🩵💚
